## handoff
- produced: Complete build-prep package: exact scaffold (12-file manifest + paths), confirmed CDN/model imports (WebLLM v0.2.84 + `@huggingface/transformers@4.2.0`), cosine-sim RAG pattern, copy-paste orders.json (10 entries) and knowledge-base.json (20 entries), ET hours snippet, typing indicator CSS+JS, full CSS design token set, widget UI specs, analytics event schema, workSamples.js entry.
- decisions: WASM is primary (CI) path; `@xenova/transformers` banned; typing indicator required for 3-8s WASM latency; keyword-match fallback for pre-embed warm-up; template-RAG as Tier 3 if WASM fails; no backend needed.
- next needs: demo-builder creates all 12 files using the exact snippets above; validates WASM Qwen2.5-0.5B returns coherent answers (not stubs); WebGPU is progressive enhancement only; Zendesk ticket card styled per Section 9; proposal-writer must flag Zendesk-as-simulated and include US-based confirmation verbatim.
- risks: Qwen2.5-0.5B WASM coherence in headless must be validated before deploy; WebGPU 600-900 MB download must not gate first-paint; `@huggingface/transformers` v4 pipeline API — if `out[0].generated_text.at(-1).content` doesn't work, try `out[0].generated_text[out[0].generated_text.length-1].content` or log the shape.
